            The paradox exists, though, because opposition to free trade depends upon
<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">two</NUMEX> antithetical ideas, both of which, interestingly enough, are wrong. The
<NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">first</NUMEX> is that free trade is lowering the standard of living in developed
<ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">countries</ENAMEX> by encouraging the migration of jobs and the creation of trade
