sectors of developed economies (textiles, <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">steel</ENAMEX>) are hurt by free trade, but
it's equally true that other sectors (computer software and hardware, financial
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">services</ENAMEX>) are helped. More to the point, the fundamental truth of free trade is
that when <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">countries</ENAMEX> produce those goods in which they have a comparative
advantage, both sides benefit, because capital ends up being allocated to its
most productive uses, which is the only way real wealth can be created.

